name: Warunk WOW KWB Bali
address: Jl. Gatot Subroto Barat No.518, Padangsambian Kaja, Bali, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80117, Indonesia

review 3:

Actually they have great ambience, DJ‚Äôs, indoor smooking area. The service were great but you have to call them more than 4 times until they notice you as the music bit loud and they didn‚Äôt always look around so that bit hard.
Also our drink came after 15 minutes after our food. Even we have to ask and they were ask our bill again so I think the kitchen forgot about our order)
Also the toast was too hard,  at first I thought it was just the edges but the whole toast does.
I ask for extra ice cream and mozarella. It‚Äôs around 6-7k/additional but see? I didn‚Äôt see even half of a scoop ice cream and they put Chocolate Sprinkles which is not everybody like it(I was just thought they might want or they think that will be seen more interesting but some people like me didn‚Äôt like it)
I ordered Avocado choco mousse, I get almost half of the glass size avocado with Avocado no sugar(I really like) and choco powder but I didn‚Äôt see any mousse. So I‚Äôm not understand what mousse they mean?
The last thing we ordered Strawberry smoothies and they gave us Mix Smoothies (banana and strawberry)üò≠ but luckly they want to change it.
So for the service was good but not for the food and how they explain their menu(details ingredient maybe) so we more understand?

Was one of the places I usually visit on the weekends. Cozy place, nice music & performer, foods‚Ä¶ so so.. but have to admit that I have experienced an unpleasant service. I was requesting a Bday surprise for a friend and the staff was ok-ing that and said it‚Äôs include as a complimentary (Free). Till the time as it‚Äôs decided, nothing came up and at the end a surprise happened but it‚Äôs not for us, it‚Äôs for another table. name: Bali Hotel | Zizz Convention Hotel
address: Jln. Mudutaki V No.2 Tegal Jaya, Dalung, Kec. Kuta Utara, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80117, Indonesia
review 1:
I stayed at Ubud for few days at 2stars hotel and it was so freaking much better than this hotel, dirty, stinky, some of the staff were very unprofessional and impolite.
The room was smelling like old sweats, no hot water for shower, dust all over window frame, someone's hairs on the floor even dead fliesü§Æ, I've been to better cheaper hotels, definitely NOT going back!!!
review 2: Recommended to enjoy a more secluded and quiet Denpasar. The room price is affordable, yet clean and comfortable for even family tourist like me. The staff is also very friendly. Recommended hotel.
review 3: Used to be really good 2 years ago l, revisited and very disappointed that the room condition has deteriorated greatly. Cleanliness still good, wifi and AC works, hot water is running, but the room itself is in dire need of renovation. Wall paint are peeled off, lots of stain around the AC unit, and the bathroom especially need a lot of renovation.
review 4: Not bad. Had to turn on the control panel every time we went in to get the room working. One bed lamp didn't work, AC remote didn't respond. Good reception service. Was a decent comfy stay.
review 5:
We spend 6 days with everyday cleaning on our cabin and it was awesome.. we slept very good and it's important for nice holidays...
- i hope they can make sandwich as breakfast also.. :) tuna sandwich maybe? Hehe..

review 1: Clean seating area and clean toilet. Spacious. Good service. Car parking space is also available and has a drive through too. WiFi good.
review 2:
Bought Matcha Cream Frappe and Cheese something pastry Cheese Danish? Hmm.. Not sure.. I forget the name üòÇ.
I asked for less sugar and they really made it with less sugar. ü•π
Both was so yummy.ü§§
The Interior Ambience and facilities are super nice, so comfortable
Restroom is super clean.
And the staff is super nice and friendly üòÜ‚ù§Ô∏è
Definitely will recommend this place to my starbucks lover friends.
review 3: This place will always be the first option if my bf and I want to continue our work. Cozy place with friendly staffs.
review 4:
Comfortable yet busy place!
I was surprised that this place is soooo crowded after 11am and i was speechless.
This Starbucks location is fairly new in town, strategically placed between Denpasar and Dalung area and you could easily spot it.
I was here (first time!) with my friend and i was a bit surprised that my ice latte venti size ‚òï was not included with sugar. SURPRISINGLY I LIKE IT! The coffee was not too bitter and i can enjoy the milk inside the mix!
Also, in the afternoon, i order Vanilla Cream venti size too! And it was  sugary, creamy, the caramel sauce on top was nice too and it looks cute! ü•õ I love it!!
Overall, the price (a bit too expensive for me) and the comfort for the place you could get (minus the crowd, obviously), i would rate this as 4.5 ‚≠ê/5!!!
I love it!
If i somehow have money, i would love to order the Latte again!

The parking area was quite spacious!
There is a drive thru place too!
They have broad options in their menu too!
They have separate area outside for smoking area which is BLESSING, i can breathe better!
The service is a bit meh, but not bad.
Would love to visit again next time!
review 5: The 500th starbucks in Indonesia, the place is beautiful they have a decent wifi, AC and toilet. They also served drive thru. Location wise is pretty strategic in my opinion. The AC is really cold (which is good during hot weather outside) this starbucks is really good for working, many charging socket. The service is really good too, like any other starbucks. The barista is friendly too. If I were close to this starbucks, maybe I‚Äôll come here everyday. But unfortunately I live far far away.

name: Sushi On The Street

review 1: The flavors were impeccably balanced, a testament to their dedication to quality ingredients. The cozy atmosphere and friendly staff add to the charm, making it an inviting spot. review 4: sushi dining place that opens late afternoon until evening. located on cargo road, clearly visible from the main road. for the taste of sushi, delicious with large portions and cheap prices. waiting for food long enough because this place is always a lot of visitors, but it's still worth it. not only sushi, the drinks are also cheap. Avocado juice is only 10 thousand. and sushi with a price range of 20 rb to 50 rb.
review 5: Japanese food with local ingredients. But delicious too. Chief is smart in processing his cooking. But music hurts my ears to hear it. Hehehe...

name: The Old Champ Caf√®
address: 957H+XF6, Jl. Mudu Taki, Dalung, Kec. Kuta Utara, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
A nice cozy place with the option of outdoor or AC room.

The food were tasty (at least for the ones we ordered), large portions with resonable price. And if you see "pedas" aka spicy in the menu, they do mean it.

The service was quite fast and the staff were friendly.

Can be very busy during weekends.
review 2:
The food was tasty, in big portions and reasonable price.

The pork ribs was delicious, love the sauce, potato wedges well cooked. If you like herbs try the green rice bowl, gonna love it.
Champion chicken comes with mash potatoes on the top of the chicken, macaroni cheese, salad. I also love mexican parmigiana and the sauce. All the food I ordered was delicious.

The place was spacious and clean. They have indoor and outdoor. Good service. Keep the good work üëç Definitely will come back.
review 3: Best family restaurant. Setup like an American diner but with amazing food (they have pizza, BBQ, Indonesian food, fries, burger etc). Food taste really good too. Big portion, so you can share with your family/friend/companion. Good price. Always busy. Waiters are really, really nice. Clean place, lots of comfortable seatings. Perhaps what could be improved is variety of beverages and/or desserts in the menu item. Would be perfect to have more coffee or tea options, for example. Really good place I keep coming here.
review 4: The old classic old champ has finally opened in gatsu, they serves wide range western grills and fry and as well as some Indonesian food! Their chicken wings will always be my favorite, it's sweet, spicy and a little bit tangy and the portion was big. Definitely gonna come again when have the chance to try their other menu.
review 5: the service was very good, especially for the portion of food that we thought was medium but it turned out to be so big that the four of us felt like our stomachs were full & yes the food was just like the picture shown
